<body bgcolor = "#BCE954">

<div class="leftFixed">
This div element is at right:7 bottom:0;
</div>



<h3>An element with position: fixed; is positioned relative to the viewport, which means it always stays in the same place even if the page is scrolled:</h3>


<h3>Right and bottom attributes function like baselines, because 'right:0' is all the way to right or to the bottom respectively.

<h3>So to go left or up, just enter an integer </h3>

<h3>Cannot go past the container, so 1000 in the body still wont break into the header </h3>

<div class="fixed">
This div element is at right:0 bottom:0;
</div>




